Cmo funcionan las opiniones y calificaciones de clientes

Las opiniones de clientes, incluidas las valoraciones de productos ayudan a que los clientes conozcan ms acerca del producto y decidan si es el producto adecuado para ellos.

Para calcular la valoracin global y el desglose porcentual por estrella, no utilizamos un promedio simple. En cambio, nuestro sistema considera cosas como la actualidad de la opinin y si el revisor compr el producto en Amazon. Tambin analiza las opiniones para verificar la confiabilidad.

3.0 de 5 estrellas Not bad but not what I expected
Calificado en Estados Unidos el 9 de abril de 2021
I received my order earlier than expected. The plants were apparently healthy and not damaged by shipping. They came bundled in a plastic sandwich baggies that were rolled in paper, and packed in a box with more paper for padding.I ordered 2 of the 10 packs of 10" - 15" trees. I actually received a total of 26 trees. They were not as advertised though. They were only 3" on average with none being larger than 4" and some being 2".The stems all had a decent root structure. The leaves are thicker and tougher that the moringa that I have seen before. The stocks are also thicker and appear that they may be clone starts from the branches of a healthy tree. I am not positive, but I don't think these are individual starts from seeds. There was no advertised description as to weather they would've from seeds or cloned branches, so this is more an observation and not a complaintAll in all, I am satisfied so far with these trees. I am disappointed that they were not as large as advertised. I wish the seller would have been straight forward with what I would really be getting. They seem to have compensated for the smaller size by adding an extra 3 trees to each pack of 10. I just wish they would have communicated this at least in a message.I will plant these (in central Texas) and see how they go from there. I will update this review if there is anything of value to add.

Carmello Young
5.0 de 5 estrellas Amazing
Calificado en Estados Unidos el 9 de julio de 2022
Compra verificada
Fast shipping and shipped with absolute care. Got these less than a week ago and potted them up in temporary homes until they fill out a little more. The pictures I posted are from today and when I tell you that they are putting on new growth I mean it. Do not be alarmed if they arrive with a few yellow leaves or if those yellow leaves drop off. That's normal. I do recommend tying them to something for support because they are some dainty lil things at this stage of growth. I just used some bamboo skewers i had around the house and jute twine so the wind is not having its way with them.
The seller packaged these with great care and for what looks like a small operation there was big thought into packaging and I even got more than what i was expecting in the form of a little pouch with some seeds in it as well. A++++

Dean Rising
3.0 de 5 estrellas Not bad but not what I expected
Calificado en Estados Unidos el 9 de abril de 2021
Compra verificada
I received my order earlier than expected. The plants were apparently healthy and not damaged by shipping. They came bundled in a plastic sandwich baggies that were rolled in paper, and packed in a box with more paper for padding.

I ordered 2 of the 10 packs of 10" - 15" trees. I actually received a total of 26 trees. They were not as advertised though. They were only 3" on average with none being larger than 4" and some being 2".

The stems all had a decent root structure. The leaves are thicker and tougher that the moringa that I have seen before. The stocks are also thicker and appear that they may be clone starts from the branches of a healthy tree. I am not positive, but I don't think these are individual starts from seeds. There was no advertised description as to weather they would've from seeds or cloned branches, so this is more an observation and not a complaint

All in all, I am satisfied so far with these trees. I am disappointed that they were not as large as advertised. I wish the seller would have been straight forward with what I would really be getting. They seem to have compensated for the smaller size by adding an extra 3 trees to each pack of 10. I just wish they would have communicated this at least in a message.

I will plant these (in central Texas) and see how they go from there. I will update this review if there is anything of value to add.
Leer ms
